'''David Strettell''' is the founder and owner of New York City’s only independent bookstore for [[photography]], Dashwood Books.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/dashwood-books-new-york-directory|title=From Helmut Newton to William Eggleston: New York's Only Store Devoted to Photo Books|work=Vogue|access-date=2018-11-25|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefutureperfect.com/present_tense/articles/dashwood-books|title=NY {{!}} Dashwood Books|last=Perfect|first=The Future|website=The Present Tense|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-25}}</ref> He opened the store in 2005. <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.anothermag.com/art-photography/1305/david-strettel-dashwood-books|title=David Strettel, Dashwood Books|last=AnOther|date=2011-08-22|work=AnOther|access-date=2018-11-25|language=en}}</ref>Prior to this, Strettell was [[Mario Testino]]’s assistant, and then the cultural director of [[Magnum Photos]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.departures.com/top-new-york-bookstores/6|title=Top New York Bookstores|website=Departures|language=en|access-date=2018-11-25}}</ref> for 12 years. He publishes books as well about photography including limited-edition monographs.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gq.com/story/checking-in-with-dashwood-books|title=Dropping In On... Dashwood Books|last=Seymour|first=Corey|date=2009-11-04|work=GQ|access-date=2018-11-25|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://archive.nytimes.com/query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage-990CE6D8123FF930A25752C1A9679D8B63.html|title=Photo Ops|access-date=2018-11-25|language=en}}</ref> Strettell is married to Ann Christiansen, and a father of one.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gq.com/story/where-the-big-ideas-come-from|title=Where the Big Ideas Come From|last=O'Brien|first=Glenn|date=2006-06-22|work=GQ|access-date=2018-11-25|language=en}}</ref>
